TALIESIN: That's seven.

01:36:00.670 --> 01:36:11.255
SAM: Four... I need one more. That's a d12.
(laughs) Oh man, these are all good, though.

01:36:11.255 --> 01:36:12.835
TALIESIN: So you want one more, though.

01:36:12.835 --> 01:36:21.734
SAM: I do. Oh my God! Okay. 16, 17, 18, 19, 20,
30, 41.

01:36:21.734 --> 01:36:27.850
MATT: 41 points of damage, nice! It slams into his
form and you watch as his body kind of tears open

01:36:27.850 --> 01:36:31.474
for a second, the flames dissipating and then form
back in, but they're starting to flicker.

01:36:31.474 --> 01:36:32.921
SAM: He's not dead?

01:36:32.921 --> 01:36:33.888
MATT: No.

01:36:33.888 --> 01:36:35.888
SAM: As my bonus action, I'll punch him again.

01:36:35.888 --> 01:36:37.090
MATT: No bonus.

01:36:37.090 --> 01:36:40.776
SAM: That was my action, as a bonus action, I can
do something else with Bigby, no?

01:36:40.776 --> 01:36:42.935
MATT: Let me double check.

01:36:42.935 --> 01:36:48.833
SAM: Every subsequent action I can do something as
a bonus action, does that also negate the action?

01:36:48.833 --> 01:36:53.798
MATT: When you cast a spell as a bonus action, it
says here you can move the hand and cause the

01:36:53.798 --> 01:37:01.935
effects. It's your bonus action to move the spell.
So your action is there, I'll say-- it says

01:37:01.935 --> 01:37:03.681
specifically bonus action.

01:37:03.681 --> 01:37:05.681
SAM: So I can't do it as my action?

01:37:05.681 --> 01:37:07.537
LAURA: So you can do something else!

01:37:07.537 --> 01:37:09.112
SAM: So that was my bonus action, then.

01:37:09.112 --> 01:37:10.342
MATT: Correct, to do that is your bonus.

01:37:10.342 --> 01:37:11.514
SAM: So I can do something else, then?

01:37:11.514 --> 01:37:13.658
MATT: I'll let you do it again if you want to.

01:37:13.658 --> 01:37:21.164
SAM: No, no, no, I'll do something else. Oh! By
the way, I can't use my movement to drink a

01:37:21.164 --> 01:37:22.385
potion, right?

01:37:22.385 --> 01:37:23.280
MATT: No.

01:37:23.280 --> 01:37:24.480
SAM: Okay (laughs).

01:37:24.480 --> 01:37:26.085
TRAVIS: (laughing) I'd like to drink a potion.

01:37:26.085 --> 01:37:31.043
SAM: Can I lean over the wall there? And I'll
Lightning Bolt the same guy.

01:37:31.043 --> 01:37:41.501
MATT: Okay. So it would be over the edge of that
wall there and (blasting noise). All right, go for

01:37:41.501 --> 01:37:52.936
it. So that's a no. That is a 12 for its dexterity
saving throw, so it takes full damage.

01:37:52.936 --> 01:37:55.386
SAM: All right, so.

01:37:55.386 --> 01:37:58.255
TALIESIN and SAM: Oh!

01:37:58.255 --> 01:38:01.548
SAM: Four ones in a row so far, so--

01:38:01.548 --> 01:38:04.105
(laughter)

01:38:04.105 --> 01:38:12.328
SAM: So I made up for some of them. 15.

01:38:12.328 --> 01:38:19.051
MATT: 15 points of lightning damage against the
fire elemental. Okay, the bolt hits it and the

01:38:19.051 --> 01:38:24.634
fire elemental goes (sizzling), not terribly
damaged by the impact.

01:38:24.634 --> 01:38:26.719
TRAVIS: At least it didn't point and laugh at you.

01:38:26.719 --> 01:38:28.560
MATT: Okay, do you want to stay where you are?

01:38:28.560 --> 01:38:30.273
SAM: Yeah, absolutely.

01:38:30.273 --> 01:38:34.465
MATT: Okay, that ends Scanlan's turn. Up to the
top: Percival.

01:38:34.465 --> 01:38:37.861
TRAVIS: He used your full first name.

01:38:37.861 --> 01:38:39.903
TALIESIN: Yeah, okay, that's fine.

01:38:39.903 --> 01:38:41.363
MARISHA: It's like when you're in trouble.

01:38:41.363 --> 01:38:45.175
TALIESIN: I am in trouble. I have a whole bunch of
your d8s over here, by the way. Feel free to pull

01:38:45.175 --> 01:38:52.666
them out whenever you like. I'm going to try a
couple things. I'm going to do a piercing shot on

01:38:52.666 --> 01:38:59.074
the fire elemental, which I think I can do. I'm
going to start moving in a northerly direction, so

01:38:59.074 --> 01:39:07.200
I guess I'll take like one or two steps southwest,
I suppose it would be to you. Yeah, there you go.

01:39:07.200 --> 01:39:08.452
MATT: There?

01:39:08.452 --> 01:39:26.860
TALIESIN: Yeah, that'll do it. And I'm going to do
a piercing shot. That burns a grit, okay. That'll

01:39:26.860 --> 01:39:33.700
do! That's 25 to hit the elemental.

01:39:33.700 --> 01:39:35.623
MATT: 25 hits.

01:39:35.623 --> 01:39:37.678
TALIESIN: And now I have to roll again for
Thordak?

01:39:37.678 --> 01:39:43.154
MATT: Well, you have to decide whether your-- if
it's a piercing shot affecting also Kima or Grog.

01:39:43.154 --> 01:39:46.599
Because it's a straight line, and it hits--
depending on how you angle it, you're either

01:39:46.599 --> 01:39:48.252
hitting Kima or you're hitting Grog.

01:39:48.252 --> 01:39:49.409
SAM: Oh shit.

01:39:49.409 --> 01:39:50.435
TALIESIN: Really?

01:39:50.435 --> 01:39:51.610
MATT: Yep.

01:39:51.610 --> 01:39:57.150
TRAVIS: I'm saying Kima's not actually attached to
a human being, just saying.

01:39:57.150 --> 01:39:59.283
TALIESIN: Kima's not short enough that it'll go
right over her head?

01:39:59.283 --> 01:40:06.147
MATT: Nope. As per the rules as designed, no.

01:40:06.147 --> 01:40:09.977
TRAVIS: I totally love Kima, I got nothing against
her. Just looking out for myself right now.

01:40:09.977 --> 01:40:15.208
MATT: She's parkouring off of the damaged wall,
trying to get into the fray with the dragon, and

01:40:15.208 --> 01:40:17.522
happens to catch where the bullet would be going.

01:40:17.522 --> 01:40:19.753
TALIESIN: Okay, that's happening, apparently.

01:40:19.753 --> 01:40:21.034
MARISHA: Are you shooting Kima?

01:40:21.034 --> 01:40:23.689
TALIESIN: It's either Kima or Grog. Although Grog
takes half damage.

01:40:23.689 --> 01:40:25.177
MATT: This is true.

01:40:25.177 --> 01:40:27.003
TRAVIS: Yeah, okay, come on.

01:40:27.003 --> 01:40:28.250
TALIESIN: You take half damage.

01:40:28.250 --> 01:40:29.738
TRAVIS: All right. I'll remember this later.

01:40:29.738 --> 01:40:31.742
MATT: So Grog it is? Roll for attack against
Grog.

01:40:31.742 --> 01:40:34.655
LAURA: I know, his head is so high. How are you
hitting Grog?

01:40:34.655 --> 01:40:36.782
TRAVIS: It's in the rules.

01:40:36.782 --> 01:40:37.951
TALIESIN: It's in the rules.

01:40:37.951 --> 01:40:43.641
MATT: In theory, from this angle, in to hit
the fire elemental and Thordak, he has to aim up.

01:40:43.641 --> 01:40:44.511
TALIESIN: 20.

01:40:44.511 --> 01:40:46.857
MATT: 20? Against Grog hits?

01:40:46.857 --> 01:40:48.011
TRAVIS: Yeah, it hits.

01:40:48.011 --> 01:40:49.606
MATT: And roll against Thordak.

01:40:49.606 --> 01:40:57.109
TALIESIN: And, no. I can't have a misfire once
I've already hit the first?

01:40:57.109 --> 01:40:58.597
MATT: Correct, only the additional attack can
misfire.

01:40:58.597 --> 01:41:00.124
TALIESIN: Okay. That's 15, that doesn't hit.

01:41:00.124 --> 01:41:01.085
SAM: So you only hit Grog.

01:41:01.085 --> 01:41:03.992
TALIESIN: I only hit Grog. No, I also hit the fire
elemental.

01:41:03.992 --> 01:41:05.508
MATT: Roll damage once.

01:41:05.508 --> 01:41:07.534
TALIESIN: Yeah, I hit the fire elemental, though.

01:41:07.534 --> 01:41:08.937
MARISHA: Maybe you'll kill it.

01:41:08.937 --> 01:41:13.284
TALIESIN: Maybe I will. Maybe it's Maybelline.
Where are my d12s, they seem to have all

01:41:13.284 --> 01:41:14.689
vanished.

01:41:14.689 --> 01:41:23.102
MARISHA: Kill it! Oh, jeez. Come on, man.

01:41:23.102 --> 01:41:25.531
TALIESIN: That's awful. 13 points of damage.

01:41:25.531 --> 01:41:33.082
MATT: Okay. Grog, you take 13 points of piercing
damage, halved to six. Round it down. Six.

01:41:33.082 --> 01:41:35.472
TALIESIN: Sorry! And the bullet gets lodged in
you.

01:41:35.472 --> 01:41:37.064
MATT: Yeah, basically.

01:41:37.064 --> 01:41:38.923
LIAM: It's there for 50 years.

01:41:38.923 --> 01:41:41.832
TALIESIN: Sorry! And then, is the fire elemental
still standing?

01:41:41.832 --> 01:41:43.127
MATT: Yes, it is.

01:41:43.127 --> 01:41:48.086
TALIESIN: I'm irritated. I'm burning another grit,
and I'm going to do a pushback on the elemental.

01:41:48.086 --> 01:42:00.814
That's actually no save, that's just a pushback. I
just have to hit. And that hits, I should have

01:42:00.814 --> 01:42:04.692
done a-- that's a 29, 32 to hit.

01:42:04.692 --> 01:42:09.415
MATT: 32 to hit. That'll hit, go ahead and roll
damage. And it just gets pushed back ten feet?

01:42:09.415 --> 01:42:11.144
TALIESIN: No, I'm saving you.

01:42:11.144 --> 01:42:14.539
MARISHA: I mean, I could have handled it.

01:42:14.539 --> 01:42:19.639
TALIESIN: 14. I want you to be able to get up
without that thing on you. 20 points of damage.

01:42:19.639 --> 01:42:27.073
And it gets pushed back ten feet. Thank you.

01:42:27.073 --> 01:42:31.141
MATT: Its form gets knocked back, coalesces again
as a flickering flame creature. It's looking hurt,

01:42:31.141 --> 01:42:34.448
it's barely keeping its form together at this
point, it's still standing.

01:42:34.448 --> 01:42:46.998
TALIESIN: I'm going to use my bonus action for a
healing surge to add 22 points to my hit points.

01:42:46.998 --> 01:42:52.680
Then I'm going to keep running, use spider to run
over that wall into that little house beneath the

01:42:52.680 --> 01:42:54.025
green dragon.

01:42:54.025 --> 01:42:55.140
MATT: All right.

01:42:55.140 --> 01:42:56.886
LIAM: Spider-climb is cool.

01:42:56.886 --> 01:42:59.868
SAM: Little house on the prairie, with the dragon
on it.

01:42:59.868 --> 01:43:01.145
TALIESIN: There we go.

01:43:01.145 --> 01:43:06.933
MATT: All right. That finishes your turn, Percy.
Now you watch as the skyship Deera pushes through

01:43:06.933 --> 01:43:11.911
some of the clouds, and you can now see a series
of small shapes as it looks like a half-dozen

01:43:11.911 --> 01:43:17.684
wyverns are currently harrying it from the sky,
attacking it. You can see some sort of combat

01:43:17.684 --> 01:43:22.387
going on on the bow of the ship, but you also
watch as two of its arballists are set up, and

01:43:22.387 --> 01:43:32.596
fire towards Thordak. That actually hits. That's
cocked. And, yeah. A 16 and a 15. With bonus, it

01:43:32.596 --> 01:43:33.791
hits both.

01:43:33.791 --> 01:43:35.687
LAURA: That's Captain Damon, right? To the
rescue!

01:43:35.687 --> 01:43:40.643
MATT: So, they're both super-heated, they are
flaming arballists, fire doesn't have an effect,

01:43:40.643 --> 01:43:50.135
but they still do piercing damage, for a total of
22 points of piercing damage. You watch these two

01:43:50.135 --> 01:43:57.730
large, thick heavy metallic piercing bolts come
arcing through, slamming into Thordak's hide. The

01:43:57.730 --> 01:44:01.304
flames flicker on the edge where it impacted,
though it has little effect, and Thordak is

01:44:01.304 --> 01:44:03.966
(insane growling).

01:44:03.966 --> 01:44:05.240
TRAVIS: Crazy motherfucker.

01:44:05.240 --> 01:44:06.725
LAURA: He's so fucking crazy.

01:44:06.725 --> 01:44:10.469
MATT: (insane growling) (maniacal laughter)

01:44:10.469 --> 01:44:11.848
SAM: Oh, god.

01:44:11.848 --> 01:44:16.142
MATT: Two of the wyverns apparently, noticing the
fray, and peel off, beginning to make their way

01:44:16.142 --> 01:44:20.876
down to where this struggle is happening.

01:44:20.876 --> 01:44:23.532
SAM: No problem. (whispered) Big problem!

01:44:23.532 --> 01:44:26.006
LIAM: This is a busy battlefield.

01:44:26.006 --> 01:44:29.311
MATT: At this point in time, I'm going to do--

01:44:29.311 --> 01:44:32.226
TALIESIN: You're having way too much fun.

01:44:32.226 --> 01:44:33.788
MATT: Yeah. Okay.

01:44:33.788 --> 01:44:36.156
SAM: Matt has been waiting a year for this.

01:44:36.156 --> 01:44:38.407
LIAM: Don't worry, sir, we didn't see you playing
