SAM: 10d20.

02:45:34.243 --> 02:45:38.110
LAURA: 10d20. 12d12.

02:45:38.110 --> 02:45:43.540
TRAVIS: 100d100s. And the universe implodes.

02:45:43.540 --> 02:45:45.651
MATT: DC 17 constitution saving throw.

02:45:45.651 --> 02:45:47.813
LAURA: He gets to save?

02:45:47.813 --> 02:45:52.463
MATT: Yes, he does. Which he makes. So he takes
half damage. So it's 6d10.

02:45:52.463 --> 02:46:00.605
LAURA: Oh! Whoa. That's okay, I'll just roll this,
'cause this is easier.

02:46:00.605 --> 02:46:12.087
LIAM: 6d10.

02:46:12.087 --> 02:46:15.101
LAURA: Oh, that was just 6d10. 32 halved.

02:46:15.101 --> 02:46:17.111
MATT: 32 halved. All right.

02:46:17.111 --> 02:46:18.374
SAM: Worth it.

02:46:18.374 --> 02:46:26.048
MATT: You release the first arrow, which goes and
strikes Thordak in the upper shoulder wing area.

02:46:26.048 --> 02:46:31.911
(growls) He turns around and goes to face you, the
