MATT: 18 points. Set your hit points to that. You
watch as your sister is thrown, her body

04:16:06.238 --> 04:16:13.080
unconscious, flung in the air like a ragdoll as it
scatters to one end of the cavern. You can see the

04:16:13.080 --> 04:16:18.351
volcanic activity billowing up from the recent
shaking of the room, as bits of the molten rock

04:16:18.351 --> 04:16:27.395
are flung across, as the green dragon face kind of
withdraws in the cave. And I think that's where

04:16:27.395 --> 04:16:28.946
we're going to pick up next year.

04:16:28.946 --> 04:16:30.951
(yelling)

04:16:30.951 --> 04:16:33.188
MATT: It's 11:22, guys! We gotta get home!

04:16:33.188 --> 04:16:36.088
SAM: Next year?! We have to wait a year?!

04:16:36.088 --> 04:16:40.217
LAURA: I have to find out if I'm for sure dead.

04:16:40.217 --> 04:16:42.201
LIAM: I got you, I got you.

04:16:42.201 --> 04:16:43.951
LAURA: I'm across the fucking room.

04:16:43.951 --> 04:16:47.808
LIAM: Doesn't matter, I can fly 500 feet, I got
you.

04:16:47.808 --> 04:16:50.976
TALIESIN: You're going to get the conclusion of
this before the next season of Westworld.

04:16:50.976 --> 04:16:52.746
LIAM: Lay on Hands, dude.

04:16:52.746 --> 04:16:55.856
SAM: No, she's dead.

04:16:55.856 --> 04:16:58.451
LIAM: No, shut up. I will kill you in the parking
lot.

04:16:58.451 --> 04:17:00.757
MATT: We will pick this up in January.

04:17:00.757 --> 04:17:05.315
TRAVIS: What was that called, those four flaming
rocks?

